<div style="font-size:90%">
<br><br>

<b>The Raul A. Rodrigo Memorial Seminar 2012: Donovan Waite Sensei (7th dan)</b><br><br><br>

(Click <a href="../photos/RaulRodrigoMemorialSeminar2012photos.php" class=black target=_black>here</a> to see photos of this concluded event.)<br><br><br>

<img src="WaiteSeminarPoster-final.jpg" />

<br><br><br>

The Donovan Waite seminar, scheduled for 2012 June 16 - 17 (Saturday - Sunday), is the third major cooperative project of Aikido Philippines, FFA, and PAPA for 2012.<br><br>

Donovan Waite is a student of Yoshimitsu Yamada Shihan. He is head instructor of Aikido of Center City, in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. He is also on the teaching staff of the New York Aikikai in New York City.<br><br>

This major seminar is being held in honor of Raul A. Rodrigo, nidan, chief instructor of Ateneo Aikido Club, who passed away on 2012 January 30.<br><br>

